          Appalling performance by us in the 1st half. Not one single player looked at the races. Watford won most, if not all, 50-50s, we made it easy for them to play and made numerous individual errors. We should've been 3 or 4 down. In the 2nd half we were excellent (particularly Oezil), did the complete opposite of the first in almost every regard and actually deserved to score a couple more than we did. Walcott had a great chance and Lucas' shot was unfortunate to not be an inch lower to go in off the underside of the bar. We possibly deserved a point based on the whole 90 minutes but given we were fortunate to only go in a couple down, I can't really argue with the result in all honesty. Even if we beat Chelsea, we are probably too far behind now. This should've been a nailed-on win and would've been had we not started like a pub team. I think the fact our players aren't scared of Wenger allows these performances to occur but responsibility has to also be placed on the players. Rubbish.
